<Content>Melasti good position We have just come back from 14 days at the Melasti Beach Resort, Legian. Overall our experience was very good, but we did have some problems. The room we booked was supposed to be pool side but it had a fence between our room and the pool so therefore wasn't exactly pool side, also we had single beds when we asked for a double. We changed rooms to one with a double and this overlooked the second pool (second floor) but it was a lovely sized room with a nice outlook, except for the bathroom. The ceiling in the bathroom leaked and looked like it was about to fall in (badly in need of repair). Overall we enjoyed our stay because of the locality and price. Our only real complaint was the food, breakfast were OK but dining in the restaurant was not so good, we had one evening meal which was terrible (steak). Luckily because of the locality there were plenty of nice eating places nearby. One good recommendation was there were a lot of regulars staying at this hotel and they had the deluxe rooms, so obviously these are the better ones to choose. Staff were OK more friendly when we tried a few words in their language. Once again overall the hotel was well priced and well situated. We did have a nice time. 
