<Author>Freak66
<Content>Loved the Melasti Beach My family and I have not long got back from Bali staying at the Melasti Beach for 6 nights. Overall we were very happy with the accommodation (we stayed in a bungalow) overlooking the main swimming pool. The the main bedroom was very large with ample cupboard space with shelving, in-room safe, TV, A/C and kettle for those early morning cuppas. The bonus for us was having a separate closed off sleeping area for our two children (aged 6  8) with two single beds (not rollaways). The bathroom was adequate (marble finish) comprising standard bath and separate shower. It was clean and the water hot. The only negative was the lighting in the main bedroom was quite poor but we were hardly in there so it didn't make a huge difference. Also blackout blinds may have prevented our children waking so early each morning!!!The buffet breakfast was plentiful - fresh fruit, pastries, your choice of bacon, mushrooms, etc. was excellent and varied each day. The highlight each morning was having a scruptious omelete cooked by the egg chef! Ample seating in the open-aired restaurant overlooking Kuta Beach was a bonus. The swimming pool was large but quite deep in sections. However there is a separate shallow section for younger children to swim in. The kids loved floating around on the complimentary noodles and jumping off the bridge into the water each day and indulging with a banana smoothie at the pool bar. Live music played in the bar (at the entrance to the hotel) each night. Drinks were reasonably priced. The highlight was definitely a pedicure and massage at the Spa Centre - indulge yourself!Overall we loved the location of the hotel - easy walking distance to Padma  Melasti Street. Plenty of good restaurants within the immediate area without having to walk too far with the kids at night. As always there is plenty of shopping to be done, the Balinese people are still as beautiful and friendly as ever. It had been 6 years since I was last in Bali but I can assure you it won't be taking us that long to go back. Each night by 6 year old asks when can we go back to Bali? I can confidently say  next year and we'll be staying at the Melasti Beach. 
