<Author>MarkQueensland
<Content>Beware this Hotel My wife and I stayed here from XMas Day until 8 January 2007 on the recommendation of our travel agent. Our usual Bali accomodation was booked out and our agent advised she had repeat customers for this hotel. We travel to Bali at least once a year sometimes more.Rooms are very big and spacious and clean - that's where it stops.Ordered Room Service - instead of Fish and Chips got a plate of chips.The food was terrible. We took some Balinese friends to lunch there on the first day and, after some prodding, even they said the food was awful. We had breakfast included but after the second day we walked up the road and bought it every morning. The food appears to be re heated day after day.Noise from the Pool area was deafening on occasions. Quite a few very loud people with very loud children.We lay on the bed one afternoon for a quick nap. There was a Jackhammer going upstairs. My wife had a quick look and they were refurbishing three rooms directly above us. My wife asked reception if we could be notified in future and if it was to continue for a long time can we be moved (no big drama just let us know). Management basically said what work even as the sound of the Jackhammer resounded throughout the foyer. Now there is a problem - they've lied. A young Aussie mother also flies in using soem Aussie venacular. She's been trying to get her young children to sleep and this is the third time she has requested something be done about the work or be moved. Management looks at her and says there is no work going on. Apparently she really let them have it.Had two cans out of the Bar Fridge and they were never replaced. About three days before we left, the whole contents of the Bar Fridge disappeared - who knows why. We had three cans of our own stuff in the there and when we left we were charged for the three cans we had purchased. We were so happy to leave we didn't even bother arguing - we just paid for them.This one is X Files stuff. The shower curtain is standard and has the rings attached hanging from a rail. About four days into the stay more than half of the rings have disappeared and half the shower curtain is dangling. We didn't take them or break them.The only thing we can come up with by way of explanation for the shower curtain and bar fridge is that if one room runs short of something or there is a breakage, they grab it from another room.When we were leaving we sat in the foyer waiting to be picked up. We heard two more complaints. One young couple had just arrived (6pm) and were told their room was not ready and that they may have to wait until 10pm. Young lady was not happy. Another older gentleman had booked two interconnecting rooms for Mum Dad and kids. The airconditioning wasn't working in one of the rooms and he was asking for it to be fixed before they moved in. Request seemed to be falling on deaf ears.If you want a big room at low cost stay there. We are not snobbish but the low cost for suite rooms is obviously the reason a lot of their repeat customers stay there. We didn't eat there or use any of the facilities - it was only a place to sleep. We have told our travel agent never again.Walked through the Padma Hotel - think we'll stay there next time. 
