<Author>jodeena
<Content>Melasti is Great Just like Bali Please Go We stayed at the Melasti for twenty days our teenage daughters had a double room and we had a double.We took a package and our budget rooms including buffet breakfast averaged out to AU$10.0 per head per night. Amazing Value!Our rooms where we stayed for the first ten nights were very basic but they had great air conditioning and cable tele. Many sounds from the street waft up but I like that I dont go away to be hearing the same noises as home although the girls thought the music from the bar at night was a bit over the top.When we werent doing stuff during the day We spent our time relaxing around one of the Three pools the Melasti has My favourite was the 'grand prix' pool which is in the shape of a big circle and the current just takes you around all day .There is also another huge pool and a smalller one located at the front of the hotel which is very quiet place to hang out .Every morning we walked down towards the Melasti restaurant for breakfast which was a buffet style and I am sure everyone will find something they like to eat I liked the yummy toast and also the omelettes and the savoury rice was nice too!. This is just beautiful overlooking the surf beach and having a lovely breakfast. On the tenth day we made a complaint to management because of some very disrpuptive tourists that had moved in making our stay uncomfortable with their drunken behaviour. Management upgraded us immediately to better rooms so we could enjoy the rest of our stay with our family in a peaceful way. You see nothing was to much trouble to make our stay a great family holiday.I cannot fault the Melasti the staff and amenities are amazing albeit astounding value Additionally there are many places near the hotel to eat and shop on my last day there i had nasi goreng meal for less than a dollar! and legian street has some fantastic shopping TIf you are a little afraid of returning to Bali I urge you to reconsider. Your luggage can be wrapped securly at Melbourne airport and the security in Bali is truly incredible but of course it is done in that beautiful Balinese way so you never ever feel intimidatedOur children are precious we would never let harm come to them We came once six months ago without the kids to make sure it was OK and safe for them Our girls had a ball brought many bargains made many friends , saw amazing things and really appreciate how lucky we are in Australia but deeply respect Bali and its beautiful peopleWe all felt safe and happy at the Melasti it was so relaxing and laid back. 
